  "name": "James 3:1–12",
  "localizedName": "James 3:1–12",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "People who teach others about Jesus are responsible for teaching what is true. They are responsible to God for the words they say. Yet it’s very hard for people to always speak what is right, good and true. Trying to do so is what James called taming or controlling the tongue."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The tongue is a small part of the body that people use to speak words. Their words show what is in their "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108419",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "heart"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". People’s words matter and make a big difference in other people’s lives. James warned his readers about doing evil with the words they speak."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Some people praise God as their Creator and "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108312",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Father"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". Yet they also curse and speak hateful things against people. God created people. Talking badly about them shows that someone doesn’t "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108355",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "love God"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " and serve him completely. That is like being a tree that doesn’t produce the fruit it’s meant to."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
